<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 9:59PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
southeastern Davidson, northwestern Anson, Montgomery, north central
Richmond, southern Randolph, Stanly and southwestern Chatham Counties
through 1045 PM EDT...
At 959 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Badin Lake, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, North Carolina Zoo, Biscoe, Seagrove,
Plyler, Fairview In Union County, Locust and Norwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for central
North Carolina.</instruction>
